.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "November 2025" "version 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.RI [ command_file ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple UNIX command interpreter written in C as part of the
Holberton School curriculum. It reads commands from standard input
or from a file and executes them, mimicking basic behavior of the
standard /bin/sh shell.

The shell supports:
.IP \[bu] 2
Execution of commands in both interactive and non-interactive modes.
.IP \[bu] 2
Handling of the PATH environment variable to locate executables.
.IP \[bu] 2
Built-in commands such as
.BR exit
and
.BR env .
.IP \[bu] 2
Error handling and proper process management using
.BR fork (2)
and
.BR execve (2) .
.IP \[bu] 2
Command line argument parsing and processing.

.SH INVOCATION
.B simple_shell
can be invoked both interactively and non-interactively.
If invoked with standard input connected to a terminal, an interactive
shell is started. Otherwise, commands are read from standard input.

.SH COMMAND EXECUTION
Commands are searched in the following order:
.IP 1. 3
Built-in commands
.IP 2. 3
Absolute or relative paths (commands starting with / or .)
.IP 3. 3
Commands in directories specified by the PATH environment variable

.SH BUILTINS
The following built-in commands are supported:
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell with status 0.
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables, one per line.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run in interactive mode:
.EX
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
main.c shell.c execute.c
($) ls -l
total 28
-rw-rw-r-- 1 user user  131 Nov 10 12:00 AUTHORS
($) env
USER=student
HOME=/home/student
PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin
($) exit
$
.EE
.TP
Run in non-interactive mode:
.EX
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
main.c shell.c execute.c
$ echo "env" | ./hsh
USER=student
HOME=/home/student
PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin
.EE

.SH EXIT STATUS
The shell returns the exit status of the last executed command.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.B simple_shell
uses the following environment variables:
.TP
.B PATH
Colon-separated list of directories to search for executable files.

.SH AUTHORS
Written by Almansour Khaled Shaden and Tariq Almutairi.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1),
.BR execve (2),
.BR fork (2),
.BR wait (2)

.SH BUGS
